TITLE: Injecting Style Rules into Sandboxed iframe
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to inject CSS style rules into a sandboxed iframe to control background appearance and hide noscript tags. The style element must not be serialized to maintain correct id-to-Node mapping.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rrweb-io/rrweb/blob/master/docs/sandbox.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const injectStyleRules: string[] = [
  'iframe { background: #f1f3f5 }',
  'noscript { display: none !important; }',
];

const styleEl = document.createElement('style');
const { documentElement, head } = this.iframe.contentDocument!;
documentElement!.insertBefore(styleEl, head);
for (let idx = 0; idx < injectStyleRules.length; idx++) {
  (styleEl.sheet! as CSSStyleSheet).insertRule(injectStyleRules[idx], idx);
}
```

